---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';
---

<Layout title="Migrating from Squarespace to AI Builders: Switch Guide">
  <StructuredData type="WebPage" data={{ name: 'Migrating from Squarespace to AI Builders', description: 'How to migrate from Squarespace to AI website builders. Export content, preserve SEO, choose right replacement.', url: 'https://aiwebsitebuilders.com/guides/migrating-from-squarespace-to-ai-builders' }} />

  <section class="bg-[#FFF8F0] py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black">Leaving Squarespace:<span class="block text-[#F5521A]">Migration Guide</span></h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mt-6">Squarespace is expensive. Here's how to switch without killing your SEO.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Why Leave Squarespace?</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">ðŸ’¸ Price</p>
          <p class="text-sm">$23-65/month adds up. Cheaper options exist with similar features.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">ðŸ”’ Lock-in</p>
          <p class="text-sm">No code export. Your site is hostage unless you keep paying.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-yellow-800 mb-2">ðŸŽ¨ Template Fatigue</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Squarespace sites look... like Squarespace sites. Framer offers more design variety.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Best Squarespace Alternatives</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-purple-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">For Portfolios: Framer</h4>
          <p class="text-sm mb-4">Better design quality (9.2 vs 8.2). Cheaper at $15-25/mo. Modern, cutting-edge templates.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-purple-600">Trade-off: Less polished galleries initially</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-blue-50 p-5 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">For WordPress Lovers: 10Web</h4>
          <p class="text-sm mb-4">WordPress with AI generation. More flexible. Cheaper at $10-60/mo. Better e-commerce.</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-blue-600">Trade-off: Requires WordPress knowledge</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Migration Steps</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">1. Export Content</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Download images. Copy text to Google Doc. Note page structure. Export blog posts if any.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">2. Choose Replacement</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Framer (portfolios) or 10Web (ecommerce). Sign up and start building.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">3. Recreate Site</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Use AI generator. Manually copy content. Recreate layout manually (takes 2-4 hours).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold mb-2">4. Set Up Redirects</p>
          <p class="text-sm">Keep Squarespace live for 30 days. Set up 301 redirects from old pages to new. Then cancel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black mb-6">Real Talk: Is It Worth It?</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-xl p-6 text-white">
        <p class="text-base mb-4">Migration takes <strong class="text-[#F5521A]">4-8 hours</strong>. You'll save $10-40/month (Squarespace is pricey).</p>
        <p class="text-base mb-4">Break-even: <strong class="text-[#F5521A]">3-8 months</strong>. After that, you're saving money.</p>
        <p class="text-base"><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Do it if:</strong> You're budget-conscious, comfortable rebuilding, want more flexibility.</p>
        <p class="text-base"><strong class="text-[#F5521A]">Stay if:</strong> You're happy with Squarespace, time-poor, non-technical.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
